WEBVTT
Kind: captions
Language: en

1
00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:07.333
See how you can switch to the Knox Manage new console, our easy-to-use portal that's integrated with the Knox Admin Portal, allowing

2
00:00:07.333 --> 00:00:11.633
you to access our suite of services all in one place!

3
00:00:11.633 --> 00:00:13.633


4
00:00:13.633 --> 00:00:17.033
To get started, click the profile icon.

5
00:00:17.033 --> 00:00:19.033


6
00:00:19.033 --> 00:00:21.733
Then click Settings.

7
00:00:21.733 --> 00:00:23.733


8
00:00:23.733 --> 00:00:28.733
Under Knox Manage, click General Settings to view console preferences.

9
00:00:28.733 --> 00:00:30.733


10
00:00:30.733 --> 00:00:39.299
Select New console as the preferred console. This switches the tenant to the new Knox Manage interface; only the Super Admin who

11
00:00:39.300 --> 00:00:42.466
created the tenant can make this change.

12
00:00:42.466 --> 00:00:44.499


13
00:00:44.500 --> 00:00:47.833
Click Save to apply the console preference.

14
00:00:47.833 --> 00:00:49.833


15
00:00:49.833 --> 00:00:53.566
Confirm that you want to switch your preferred console.

16
00:00:53.566 --> 00:00:55.166


17
00:00:57.100 --> 00:00:57.533


18
00:00:57.533 --> 00:01:01.366
You've now switched to the Knox Manage new console

19
00:01:01.366 --> 00:01:05.232
where you can access our device management features right from the Knox Admin Portal.

20
00:01:05.233 --> 00:01:06.199


21
00:01:06.200 --> 00:01:09.966
Let's have a look at your profiles and policies on the new console.

22
00:01:09.966 --> 00:01:11.999


23
00:01:12.000 --> 00:01:19.766
Your profiles and polices from the original console are automatically migrated to the new console, ready to be applied to your devices.

24
00:01:19.766 --> 00:01:26.866
Note that if you want to modify a profile or policy that was migrated to the new console, you'll have to return to the original console to make

25
00:01:26.866 --> 00:01:28.766
the modification.

26
00:01:28.766 --> 00:01:30.632


27
00:01:30.633 --> 00:01:38.399
You can also configure "Administrators and Roles" for Knox Manage on the Knox Admin Portal, which allows you to create custom roles

28
00:01:38.400 --> 00:01:45.266
for your sub-admins. Note that roles and permissions you set on the original console aren't migrated to the new console, and

29
00:01:45.266 --> 00:01:50.266
permissions set on the new console only apply to management actions on the new console.

30
00:01:50.266 --> 00:01:52.866


31
00:01:52.866 --> 00:01:55.799
Click the ROLES tab to manage roles.

32
00:01:55.800 --> 00:01:58.366


33
00:01:58.366 --> 00:02:01.966
Click CREATE ROLE to start creating a new role.

34
00:02:01.966 --> 00:02:04.299


35
00:02:04.300 --> 00:02:09.200
From the dropdown, select Knox Manage as the target service for the role.

36
00:02:09.200 --> 00:02:11.933


37
00:02:11.933 --> 00:02:14.199
Enter a descriptive role name.

38
00:02:14.200 --> 00:02:16.833


39
00:02:16.833 --> 00:02:24.899
You can set granular permissions for this custom role, giving you fine-grained control over what actions your Knox Manage sub-admins

40
00:02:24.900 --> 00:02:25.900
can perform.

41
00:02:25.900 --> 00:02:28.366


42
00:02:28.366 --> 00:02:36.932
For example, you can allow sub-admins on this role to create and edit profiles, but not delete profiles on Knox Manage. You can even restrict

43
00:02:36.933 --> 00:02:41.333
management actions to specific profiles on Knox Manage.

44
00:02:41.333 --> 00:02:43.266


45
00:02:43.266 --> 00:02:45.099
Click Save to create the new role.

46
00:02:45.100 --> 00:02:48.233


47
00:02:48.233 --> 00:02:56.899
You can now assign granular permissions to sub-admins on the Knox Manage new console. To learn more about Knox Manage, see our

48
00:02:56.900 --> 00:03:04.366
documentation at docs.samsungknox.com. Thanks for watching!
